comments: As always with surveys I missed some details or possibilities for certain questions. The doctor tasks were especially hard to answer, because you can never know for sure, that the surgery would be a success and you end up killing a person and failing to save the others, so it might only be death all around in the end. Even the assumption, that it was a 100 % success, was impossible for me, because I know that something can go wrong and the guy in the coma might wake up, if I don't kill him. His rights are the rights of us all and I wouldn't want to be killed in his position (possibly aware all the time). So it's really bad luck there, that the others had the accident (possibly their own fault), but I couldn't betray my principles without better reason. I let the immune guy pass, because his blood might contain the key to an antidote. So I would escort his boat and call coast guards to evacuate the harbor and prepare a quarantine for the man where doctors can research the virus and his immune system. So in most cases I was asking myself: "Oookay, I wouldn't give up on the options 'shouting', 'finding another way' and 'finding something else' than the next human being I can find to throw it in (WTF?)" - Okay, enough feedback. I wish you success with your studies.
